From 371fabde81e483076be81f2bed328c4207963981 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Avula Sri Charan <asrichar@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Sep 2025 20:18:13 +0530
Subject: UPSTREAM:CP: wifi: ath12k: Skip adding inactive partner vdev info in ml_arg's

In case of AP+STA once the vdev start is done, when supplicant triggers
a scan all the vdev's on that radio will be stopped. But on the vdev
start of other radios inactive vdev's info is being advertised as
partner links which is incorrect.

So check on arvif->is_started instead of is_created to decide if a vdev
is active or not and skip adding it as partner link if not active.

Signed-off-by: Avula Sri Charan <asrichar@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
index af6bd42..42570a0 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -16912,7 +16912,7 @@ ath12k_mac_mlo_get_vdev_args(struct ath12k_link_vif *arvif,
 		if (arvif == arvif_p)
 			continue;
 
-		if (!arvif_p->is_created)
+		if (!arvif_p->is_started)
 			continue;
 
 		if (ath12k_mac_is_bridge_vdev(arvif_p)) {
-- 
